import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['precipitation'] = pd.to_numeric(data['precipitation'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['precipitation'])
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='precipitation', bins=20, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.boxplot(x=data['temp_max'], color='lightblue')
    chart.axvline(x=data['temp_max'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['temp_max'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title("What is the average maximum temperature in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['weather'] = data['weather'].astype('category')
    sns.set_style('whitegrid')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='weather', data=data, palette='pastel')
    for p in chart.patches:
        chart.annotate(format(p.get_height(), '.0f'), (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha = 'center', va = 'center', xytext = (0, 10), textcoords = 'offset points')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition observed in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['temp_range'] = data['temp_max'] - data['temp_min']
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='temp_range', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['temp_range'].median(), color='red', label=f'Median: {data["temp_range"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature range (temp_max - temp_min) in Seattle from 2012 to 2015?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
